3174   // through the back-edge of a loop. Folding a GEP into itself means that
3175   // the value of the previous iteration needs to be stored in the meantime,
3176   // thus requiring an additional register variable to be live, but not
3177   // actually achieving anything (the GEP still needs to be executed once per
3178   // loop iteration).
